## Java Solution

```java id="jlwm54"
class KthLargest {

    PriorityQueue<Integer> minHeap;
    int k;

    public KthLargest(int k, int[] nums) {

        this.k = k;
        minHeap = new PriorityQueue<>();

        for (int num : nums) {

            minHeap.offer(num);

            if (minHeap.size() > k) {
                minHeap.poll();
            }
        }
    }

    public int add(int val) {

        minHeap.offer(val);

        if (minHeap.size() > k) {
            minHeap.poll();
        }

        return minHeap.peek();
    }
}
```

---

## Complexity Analysis

| Operation   | Time Complexity |
| ----------- | --------------- |
| Constructor | O(n log k)      |
| add()       | O(log k)        |
| peek()      | O(1)            |

**Space Complexity:** `O(k)`

Reason:

The heap stores at most **k elements**.

